3
• macOS Environment Management:
o Serve as a subject matter expert for macOS desktop engineering, providing advanced troubleshooting and support for complex issues.
o Develop and maintain standard macOS build processes, deployments, and configurations.
o Package, test, and deploy applications and software updates across the macOS environment using Jamf.
o Implement and manage security policies and compliance standards on macOS devices.
o Develop and maintain automation scripts (e.g., Shell/Bash) to streamline macOS management tasks.
o Monitor the health and performance of the macOS environment, proactively identifying and resolving potential issues.
o Participate in the evaluation and implementation of new macOS technologies and tools.
• Jamf MDM Administration:
o Administer and maintain our Jamf Pro environment, ensuring its stability, security, and optimal performance.
o Develop and implement MDM policies, profiles, and configurations to manage macOS devices effectively.
o Manage device enrollment, inventory, and compliance within Jamf.
o Troubleshoot issues related to device enrollment, configuration, and application deployment via Jamf.
o Develop and maintain Jamf scripts and API integrations to automate tasks and extend functionality.
o Stay up-to-date on the latest Jamf features and best practices.
• Troubleshooting and Support:
o Provide Tier 3/4 level support for macOS and Jamf-related incidents and service requests.
o Analyze and resolve complex technical issues, documenting solutions and contributing to knowledge base articles.
o Collaborate with other IT teams (e.g., Security, Networking) to resolve cross-functional issues.
• Project and Documentation:
o Lead or participate in projects related to macOS and Jamf infrastructure upgrades, migrations, and new deployments.
o Create and maintain comprehensive technical documentation, including standard operating procedures, configuration guides, and troubleshooting steps.
• Continuous Improvement:
o Identify opportunities for process improvements and automation within the macOS and Jamf management workflows.
o Research and recommend new technologies and best practices to enhance the end-user experience and improve efficiency.
o Mentor and provide guidance to support teams.
Qualifications:
• 10+years of experience in desktop engineering with a strong focus on macOS.
• Strong scripting skills for automation and system administration.
• Extensive experience administering and troubleshooting Jamf Pro in a corporate environment.
• Deep understanding of macOS operating system internals, file systems, and security principles.
• Proven ability to package and deploy applications and software updates on macOS using Jamf.
• Experience with Microsoft Active Directory and Entra ID in a macOS environment.
• Solid understanding of networking concepts (TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP).
• Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and troubleshooting skills.
• Strong communication, collaboration, and interpersonal skills.
• Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment.
• Excellent documentation skills.
